The initial stage of complex studying of the Polish language (the basic knowledge on phonetics, morphology and lexicon, reading of texts and purchase of elementary colloqual and written skills).

Main discussion topics:
1. introducing yourself
2. basic communication phrases
3. names of objects, animals, plants
4. family
5. hobby
6. in a restaurant
7. shopping
8. time
9. polish holidays in autumn and winter

Main grammar issues:
1. conjugations
2. present and past tense forms
3. modal verbs
4. declination (nominative, genitive, accusative, instrumental)
5. numeralsObjectives/eesmärkid:  To give students the basic information about Polish language, its phonetics, morphology and lexicon, to develop skills of pronunciation and reading.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student, who passed the first part of the course of Polish language (A1.2), acquires initial knowledge of the language, expands the knowledge of features of other slavic languages.
